aybe the Groovy MetaClass doesn’t invoke class$ because it treats the method as static and synthetic, considering \\\"class$\\\" as a property instead. But the test passed, which raises questions. Perhaps it’s resolvedClass rather than class$ that’s causing this? It’s all a bit strange, making me ponder how the MetaClass handles class$ in different scenarios.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating code implementation**\\n\\nI'm considering how to use the `InvokerHelper.invokeStaticMethod` with `MapCreator.class`. It might be similar to `metaClass`, but I'm not entirely sure. I believe `MethodHandles` is pretty robust, so I should probably add the necessary imports and handle Throwable properly. I'll think about using `assertEquals`. Should I remove the `MetaClass` import? Maybe I should keep both for flexibility. I need to make sure the `MethodHandle` approach covers my requirements comprehensively.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_vIrXEFWIDWQSmnNXfhhD28wx|fc_00de02aaea8bb629016a270bebbb448193ac3df209bb84a3b2", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/src/test/java/io_rest_assured/rest_assured/MapCreatorTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.io.IOException;\nimport java.net.HttpURLConnection;\nimport java.net.InetSocketAddress;\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\nimport java.util.List;\n", "newText": "import java.io.IOException;\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodHandle;\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodHandles;\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodType;\nimport java.net.HttpURLConnection;\nimport java.net.InetSocketAddress;\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\nimport java.util.List;\n"}, {"oldText": "import com.sun.net.httpserver.Headers;\nimport com.sun.net.httpserver.HttpExchange;\nimport com.sun.net.httpserver.HttpServer;\nimport groovy.lang.MetaClass;\nimport io.restassured.internal.MapCreator;\n", "newText": "import com.sun.net.httpserver.Headers;\nimport com.sun.net.httpserver.HttpExchange;\nimport com.sun.net.httpserver.HttpServer;\nimport io.restassured.internal.MapCreator;\n"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    void groovyMetaClassResolvesGeneratedClassHelper() {\n        MapCreator mapCreator = new MapCreator();\n        MetaClass metaClass = mapCreator.getMetaClass();\n        String markerClassName = \"io.restassured.internal.NoParameterValue\";\n\n        Object resolvedClass = metaClass.invokeStaticMethod(\n                MapCreator.class,\n                \"class$\",\n                new Object[] {markerClassName});\n\n        assertEquals(markerClassName, ((Class<?>) resolvedClass).getName());\n    }\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    void generatedGroovyClassHelperResolvesLibraryClassName() throws Throwable {\n        MethodHandles.Lookup lookup = MethodHandles.privateLookupIn(MapCreator.class, MethodHandles.lookup());\n        MethodHandle classHelper = lookup.findStatic(\n                MapCreator.class,\n                \"class$\",\n                MethodType.methodType(Class.class, String.class));\n        String markerClassName = \"io.restassured.internal.NoParameterValue\";\n\n        Object resolvedClass = classHelper.invoke(markerClassName);\n\n        assertEquals(markerClassName, ((Class<?>) resolvedClass).getName());\n    }\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1061, "output": 1618, "cacheRead": 66048, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 68727, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780943820550, "responseId": "resp_00de02aaea8bb629016a270bcd28408193b79c2a7788e50dc6"}}
